260
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,880
-Good morning, sir.
-Good morning, Captain.

261
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,390
-What time is it?
-Five.

262
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:53,830
Not long now, then.

263
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,870
No, sir.

264
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:09,680
Lookouts aloft, Mr Learmouth?  

265
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:10,790
They've been up for half an hour.

266
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:13,550
-And the horizon?
-Horizon!

267
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:18,390
-Horizon clear!
-Horizon clear!

268
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:21,630
Thank you, Mr Learmouth. Let's put an end to this.

269
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:26,260
Mr Seward, I want all hands to quarters within the hour.

270
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:30,870
Mr Learmouth, set a new course, please, south-southwest.

271
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,390
If there are any complaints about the delay,

272
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:36,550
