I made it myself some time ago, but I'm sure I can still find it.

1009
01:12:52,640 --> 01:12:56,110
Help yourself. It's a funny-looking thing, isn't it? 

1010
01:12:56,110 --> 01:12:57,470
Yes, it is a funny-looking thing.

1011
01:12:58,320 --> 01:13:00,270
Do you think I could have a chair?

1012
01:13:04,640 --> 01:13:06,590
-Thank you.
-Look, er...

1013
01:13:09,880 --> 01:13:11,830
Are you all right?

1014
01:13:13,480 --> 01:13:15,430
No, I don't think I am.

1015
01:13:18,400 --> 01:13:19,950
How old are you?

1016
01:13:20,040 --> 01:13:23,350
18, although I don't know what that's got to do with it.

1017
01:13:25,040 --> 01:13:27,990
Nothing. Nothing at all. Don't take any notice of me.

1018
01:13:29,680 --> 01:13:31,430
It's just...

1019
01:13:32,320 --> 01:13:34,270
Do you have any idea what it's like?

1020
01:13:34,360 --> 01:13:37,670
War? Is that what you're worried about?

1021
01:13:38,520 --> 01:13:40,470
It'll all be over before it begins.

1022
01:13:40,560 --> 01:13:44,100
Germany don't want a war. It's just their way of waking us all up.

1023
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:47,960
Look, can I get you something?

1024
01:13:48,040 --> 01:13:49,990
-A cup of tea?
-Yes.

1025
01:13:51,600 --> 01:13:53,550
A cup of tea. That'll do the trick.

1026
01:14:21,760 --> 01:14:23,550
I suggest they go to different destinations, 

1027
01:14:23,550 --> 01:14:26,110
then, if one is destroyed, the others will survive.

1028
01:14:26,200 --> 01:14:28,230
-Is that possible?
-I'll do my best.

1029
01:14:28,320 --> 01:14:31,910
At the moment, it's all I can do to get everything over to Cambridge.

1030
01:14:32,000 --> 01:14:33,800
Oh, we are sending some of the smaller items to 

1031
01:14:33,800 --> 01:14:36,230
a science museum vault in Beckenham.

1032
01:14:36,320 --> 01:14:37,440
I could try and get one in there.

1033
01:14:37,440 --> 01:14:39,270
Yes, Beckenham would be good.

1034
01:14:39,360 --> 01:14:42,110
Well, leave it with me and I'll sort something out.

1035
01:14:42,200 --> 01:14:44,150
Where are you going with that?

1036
01:14:56,880 --> 01:14:58,830
Whoa! Watch where you're going!

1037
01:15:46,920 --> 01:15:48,870
Muriel?

1038
01:15:48,960 --> 01:15:50,910
Muriel!

1039
01:15:53,920 --> 01:15:55,870
-Is that you?
-Rupert?

1040
01:15:59,040 --> 01:16:00,990
I've just had...

1041
01:16:03,600 --> 01:16:05,750
Rupert? Rupert, is that you?

1042
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:27,750
-Where's he gone?
-Down there.

1043
01:18:22,040 --> 01:18:23,630
They're all satisfied.

1044
01:18:23,720 --> 01:18:26,670
Now, if we just put the watch together and take it to the committee,

1045
01:18:26,760 --> 01:18:28,750
they'll give us half the prize.

1046
01:18:28,840 --> 01:18:30,790
What watch?

1047
01:18:30,880 --> 01:18:32,830
There is no watch.

1048
01:18:34,320 --> 01:18:36,270
Look at it.

1049
01:18:55,360 --> 01:18:59,110
You know, the strange thing is I want to build another one.

1050
01:18:59,920 --> 01:19:04,270
Taking it apart and putting it together again, I can see improvements.

1051
01:19:04,360 --> 01:19:07,670
You have to make a duplicate. Those were the terms.

1052
01:19:07,760 --> 01:19:09,710
Terms?

1053
01:19:09,800 --> 01:19:13,750
What do they know? There wasn't one of them who understood what I was saying.

1054
01:19:13,840 --> 01:19:16,300
Even the watchmakers didn't see everything.

1055
01:19:16,400 --> 01:19:18,350
They think in straight lines,

1056
01:19:18,440 --> 01:19:20,950
not prepared for the curve,

1057
01:19:21,040 --> 01:19:24,390
the line of surprise that takes you to a place you cannot see.

1058
01:19:30,440 --> 01:19:31,330
And how are we to know that 

1059
01:19:31,330 --> 01:19:34,470
this is the same watch that was used at the disclosure?

1060
01:19:34,560 --> 01:19:37,060
If I could make a watch in five days, 

1061
01:19:37,060 --> 01:19:39,070
then I'd have the prize money by the end of the week.

1062
01:19:42,000 --> 01:19:47,150
Very well. I am pleased to offer you the certificate of this Board.

1063
01:19:47,240 --> 01:19:48,710
Congratulations.

1064
01:19:48,800 --> 01:19:50,750
You've made something useful.

1065
01:19:51,900 --> 01:19:55,820
How long will it take you to make two further watches, as required by the Act?

1066
01:19:55,920 --> 01:19:59,790
-The new Act.
-I beg your pardon, sir?

1067
01:19:59,880 --> 01:20:03,790
Additional instruments are not required by the Act of Queen Anne.

1068
01:20:03,880 --> 01:20:06,870
The Act required that the invention be practical.

1069
01:20:06,960 --> 01:20:11,080
We have merely clarified that issue in our recent amendment. 

1070
01:20:11,080 --> 01:20:12,390
How long will it take?

1071
01:20:12,480 --> 01:20:16,590
Two years, if my watch is returned to me to work on.

1072
01:20:17,720 --> 01:20:19,670
I'm afraid that is impossible.

1073
01:20:19,760 --> 01:20:22,350
Your watch, as you call it, is, of course, our watch.

1074
01:20:22,440 --> 01:20:26,110
And this Board intends, under the direction of the Astronomer Royal,

1075
01:20:26,200 --> 01:20:29,310
to conduct a series of tests, at the observatory in Greenwich,

1076
01:20:29,400 --> 01:20:33,430
at the conclusion of which, Mr Larkin Kendall will make a copy of the watch

1077
01:20:33,520 --> 01:20:36,270
and, I think you will agree, his need is the greater.

1078
01:20:37,440 --> 01:20:40,110
It will take a further year if I'm forced to work without it.

1079
01:20:41,600 --> 01:20:44,670
So be it, Mr Harrison. So be it.

1080
01:20:45,880 --> 01:20:48,030
Thank you.

1081
01:20:52,720 --> 01:20:54,670
Mr Harrison...

1082
01:20:55,880 --> 01:21:00,350
I have instructed the Astronomer Royal to collect the rest of the timepieces.

1083
01:21:02,240 --> 01:21:04,190
Why?

1084
01:21:04,280 --> 01:21:06,710
Because they are the property of this Board.

1085
01:21:24,080 --> 01:21:26,950
He has brought an open cart with no suspension.

1086
01:21:27,040 --> 01:21:29,990
He means to destroy them on the journey to Greenwich.

1087
01:21:33,600 --> 01:21:37,030
-Good morning. I have come...
-I know why you're here.

1088
01:21:37,120 --> 01:21:39,190
-Mr Harrison.
-Reverend Maskelyne.

1089
01:21:39,280 --> 01:21:41,230
The machines are ready for collection.

1090
01:21:41,320 --> 01:21:44,150
I will need a certificate from you that they're in good order.

1091
01:21:44,240 --> 01:21:45,900
I'm not sure I'm a good judge of that, sir. 

1092
01:21:45,900 --> 01:21:47,510
For once, I agree with you.

1093
01:21:47,600 --> 01:21:50,160
I can state that they appear to be in good order.

1094
01:21:50,240 --> 01:21:52,500
I can state as a fact they're in perfect order.  

1095
01:21:52,500 --> 01:21:53,710
That will not be necessary.

1096
01:21:53,710 --> 01:21:55,900
I will need it to be understood that when they left my property,

1097
01:21:55,900 --> 01:21:57,200
that was the case, 

1098
01:21:57,200 --> 01:22:01,220
and that you are entirely responsible for their safety from this moment on.

1099
01:22:01,320 --> 01:22:02,640
I accept that responsibility. 

1100
01:22:02,640 --> 01:22:04,790
What is their normal method of transport?

1101
01:22:04,880 --> 01:22:07,110
-Boat.
-Do not bandy words with me, sir.

1102
01:22:07,200 --> 01:22:09,630
I am serious. They should go to Greenwich by barge,

1103
01:22:09,720 --> 01:22:12,590
not some old cart like a butcher would carry a bag of bones in.

1104
01:22:12,680 --> 01:22:14,300
I merely wish to know whether it is the custom 

1105
01:22:14,300 --> 01:22:16,630
to take them to pieces before moving them.

1106
01:22:16,720 --> 01:22:18,670
-No.
-But they must...

1107
01:22:18,760 --> 01:22:22,710
Enough, enough! He has the authority of the Board. Let him exercise it.

1108
01:22:23,880 --> 01:22:25,210
This is quite childish. 

1109
01:22:25,210 --> 01:22:27,150
I know perfectly well how to achieve this.

1110
01:22:29,680 --> 01:22:34,150
This is the case. We will need a... a blacksmith to help us take it apart.

1111
01:22:43,600 --> 01:22:45,550
One, two, three...

1112
01:23:27,120 --> 01:23:29,550
Your father has been cruelly used,

1113
01:23:29,640 --> 01:23:32,910
but while I'm out of the admiralty, there is little I can do.

1114
01:23:34,520 --> 01:23:36,470
But there must be some other way.

1115
01:23:37,000 --> 01:23:39,990
He cannot finish two further watches. It would kill him.

1116
01:23:41,440 --> 01:23:44,030
Do you have any skill at cards, Mr Harrison?

1117
01:23:45,400 --> 01:23:47,350
-No, my lord.
-No.

1118
01:23:47,440 --> 01:23:49,710
Neither do these ladies, it would appear.

1119
01:23:49,800 --> 01:23:52,230
Perhaps they flatter me.

1120
01:23:54,440 --> 01:23:57,910
Well, parliament has already been the instrument of much mischief.

1121
01:23:58,000 --> 01:24:01,620
There is, therefore, only one court of appeal I could recommend.

1122
01:24:01,720 --> 01:24:04,150
-And that is?
-The Crown.

1123
01:24:25,440 --> 01:24:28,270
-Could I have a look at that?
-A look at what?

1124
01:24:29,320 --> 01:24:31,780
-Your watch.
-Sit up.

1125
01:24:39,280 --> 01:24:41,230
Down you go.

1126
01:24:42,720 --> 01:24:44,670
They took mine away.

1127
01:24:56,120 --> 01:24:58,070
Here you are.

1128
01:25:04,880 --> 01:25:07,870
Mind you look after it, or you'll get me into trouble.

1129
01:25:10,040 --> 01:25:11,990
Thank you.

1130
01:25:14,480 --> 01:25:19,470
It will be quite informal. Just bow, and address him as Your Majesty.

1131
01:25:19,560 --> 01:25:22,540
I will divert the Queen, 

1132
01:25:22,540 --> 01:25:26,070
whose taste is more inclined to scandal than to science.

1133
01:25:33,080 --> 01:25:36,670
Oh. It's the enemy! It's the enemy!

1134
01:25:37,480 --> 01:25:39,940
I see we are to meet the entire family.

1135
01:25:40,040 --> 01:25:42,470
His Majesty is a most conscientious father.

1136
01:25:44,440 --> 01:25:46,390
Shh... Quiet, everyone.

1137
01:25:48,120 --> 01:25:50,580
.. with that one. Go on, pass it on.

1138
01:25:50,680 --> 01:25:52,630
-Yes, sir.
-It's "Aye aye, sir"!

1139
01:25:52,720 --> 01:25:54,670
Fire!

1140
01:25:56,560 --> 01:25:59,510
Hold your fire, gentlemen. Hold your fire.

1141
01:26:00,000 --> 01:26:04,070
My dears, we are saved. Lord Sandwich knows about the running of the ship.

1142
01:26:04,160 --> 01:26:06,110
He will come to our rescue.

1143
01:26:06,200 --> 01:26:09,070
Your Majesty, may I present Mr John Harrison?

1144
01:26:10,040 --> 01:26:13,070
Mr Harrison. I am very pleased to make your acquaintance.

1145
01:26:13,160 --> 01:26:15,720
Please, excuse our exuberance.

1146
01:26:15,800 --> 01:26:18,310
Mr William Harrison.

1147
01:26:18,400 --> 01:26:21,110
-Have you sailed on a frigate, sir?
-I have, Your Majesty.

1148
01:26:21,200 --> 01:26:24,510
-And where, pray, were the mortars situated?
-On the fo'c's'le deck.

1149
01:26:24,600 --> 01:26:28,220
Ah-ha! Georgie, you are in the right, sir, and I am in the wrong.

1150
01:26:28,320 --> 01:26:30,990
Mr Harrison will show you the positioning of your mortars.

1151
01:26:31,080 --> 01:26:33,030
You may need some more ammunition.

1152
01:26:34,800 --> 01:26:39,070
My dear, you mustn't get the children so excited. They'll never sleep.

1153
01:26:45,200 --> 01:26:49,430
Mr Harrison, I think I have something here that might interest you.

1154
01:26:49,520 --> 01:26:52,190
Please excuse my husband.

1155
01:26:52,280 --> 01:26:54,310
Come and look at our battleships, Mama.

1156
01:26:54,400 --> 01:26:56,630
May I come aboard?

1157
01:26:57,680 --> 01:27:00,240
This was presented to me by Mr Priestly,

1158
01:27:00,520 --> 01:27:03,990
a most wonderful creation for the production of electricity.

1159
01:27:04,080 --> 01:27:05,710
And what is its use?  

1160
01:27:05,710 --> 01:27:08,030
I haven't the foggiest, but dashed pretty, what?

1161
01:27:10,280 --> 01:27:13,350
Mr Harrison, I have been informed at length about your trials,

1162
01:27:13,440 --> 01:27:16,150
and I must tell you that we are very disturbed by the news.

1163
01:27:16,240 --> 01:27:18,590
The safety of our ships is our dearest concern,

1164
01:27:18,680 --> 01:27:21,470
and we are most grateful for your endeavours on their behalf.

1165
01:27:21,560 --> 01:27:23,750
Thank you, Your Majesty.

1166
01:27:23,840 --> 01:27:26,950
-Have you started work on the new watch?
-I have, sir.

1167
01:27:27,040 --> 01:27:30,820
When it is finished, will you do something for me? Let me see it.

1168
01:27:30,920 --> 01:27:32,790
I would be most interested.

1169
01:27:34,080 --> 01:27:37,350
Oh, have you seen this? I wore it today, especially for you.

1170
01:27:37,440 --> 01:27:41,550
-Mr Arnold made it for me. -Papa! Come and see our mortars!

1171
01:27:41,640 --> 01:27:44,590
-We've blown up Lord Sandwich. -I hope not!

1172
01:27:44,680 --> 01:27:47,030
The admiralty may want him back.

1173
01:27:55,520 --> 01:27:57,470
So, do I get my watch back, then?

1174
01:28:02,600 --> 01:28:04,870
I'm not sure I can do without it yet.

1175
01:28:14,640 --> 01:28:16,790
Have you had a walk today?

1176
01:28:23,960 --> 01:28:26,590
I'm getting you up. Do you have a name?

1177
01:28:29,120 --> 01:28:31,070
Rupert.

1178
01:28:31,160 --> 01:28:33,990
-Do you?
-Grace.

1179
01:28:35,960 --> 01:28:38,070
But it's Nurse Ingrams to you.

1180
01:28:58,520 --> 01:29:00,470
What do you think?

1181
01:29:02,840 --> 01:29:05,190
It's good.

1182
01:29:05,280 --> 01:29:07,470
Fit for a king?

1183
01:29:18,480 --> 01:29:20,430
Rupert?

1184
01:29:25,240 --> 01:29:27,190
Rupert...

1185
01:29:28,720 --> 01:29:31,070
It's all right. I'm here.

1186
01:29:33,680 --> 01:29:36,140
Rupert, there's nothing to be alarmed about.

1187
01:29:36,240 --> 01:29:38,190
It's only a drill.

1188
01:29:49,360 --> 01:29:51,310
Feel the time.

1189
01:29:57,200 --> 01:29:58,830
I can feel your heart.

1190
01:30:00,000 --> 01:30:01,950
That's better.

1191
01:30:03,440 --> 01:30:06,270
Finish the story you were telling me yesterday,

1192
01:30:06,360 --> 01:30:08,430
about him taking the watch to the King.

1193
01:30:10,280 --> 01:30:12,230
Did he?

1194
01:30:15,200 --> 01:30:17,830
Yes, he did.

1195
01:30:20,280 --> 01:30:24,430
The King decided to do his own experiment,

1196
01:30:27,280 --> 01:30:30,820
an experiment that lasted... months.

1197
01:30:31,720 --> 01:30:33,670
Did it work?

1198
01:30:33,760 --> 01:30:35,290
No, not at the beginning.

1199
01:30:35,290 --> 01:30:37,670
At the beginning, it was a disaster.

1200
01:30:37,760 --> 01:30:39,910
It is a most perplexing matter.

1201
01:30:40,000 --> 01:30:42,500
Dr Demainbray, my astronomer and dear friend, 

1202
01:30:42,500 --> 01:30:44,200
came to me this morning with the news.

1203
01:30:44,200 --> 01:30:46,200
Well, I can tell you, sir, that I did not believe it. 

1204
01:30:46,200 --> 01:30:48,900
I came here to see for myself, and he was right.

1205
01:30:48,900 --> 01:30:51,510
Absolutely and utterly correct, I don't know what to make of it.

1206
01:30:51,600 --> 01:30:54,190
-I don't understand. What was wrong?
-Wrong? What?

1207
01:30:54,280 --> 01:30:57,270
-Was it slow? Did it stop?
-I would that it had, sir.

1208
01:30:57,360 --> 01:30:59,200
No, the problem is more serious than that.

1209
01:30:59,200 --> 01:31:02,230
Your watch, sir, your watch, sir, is going backwards.

1210
01:31:10,040 --> 01:31:15,350
I noticed it this morning, sir, and I immediately informed His Majesty.

1211
01:31:16,600 --> 01:31:22,350
The er... The position, I believe, is correct.

1212
01:31:23,320 --> 01:31:25,270
The position is fine.

1213
01:31:25,360 --> 01:31:27,590
I have no explanation for this.

1214
01:31:27,680 --> 01:31:29,950
-Wait.
-What?

1215
01:31:30,040 --> 01:31:33,430
-The compass needles. What do you think?
-The needles?

1216
01:31:33,520 --> 01:31:36,710
When we were magnetising the needles, what did we do with the...?

1217
01:31:36,800 --> 01:31:40,300
-Whatever do you call it?
-The lodestones.

1218
01:31:40,800 --> 01:31:44,830
-Where's the key? The key...
-Quick, man, quick! Check your waistcoat.

1219
01:31:49,640 --> 01:31:51,590
Ah...

1220
01:31:52,560 --> 01:31:54,510
Lodestones.

1221
01:31:54,600 --> 01:31:58,630
-You think the magnets affected the clock?
-I am sure of it, sir.

1222
01:31:58,720 --> 01:32:01,070
Take these out and throw them in the garden.

1223
01:32:02,960 --> 01:32:04,910
Immediately.

1224
01:32:08,560 --> 01:32:10,510
There.

1225
01:32:10,600 --> 01:32:13,190
Now we must start all over again.

1226
01:32:13,280 --> 01:32:15,950
-Your Majesty is very kind.
-Piffle, sir.

1227
01:32:16,040 --> 01:32:18,110
I'm a scientist.

1228
01:32:22,160 --> 01:32:24,110
That's it.

1229
01:32:26,760 --> 01:32:29,140
That's right, watch the ball.

1230
01:32:33,120 --> 01:32:35,990
55, 56, 57...

1231
01:32:36,080 --> 01:32:37,790
58, 59...

1232
01:32:38,800 --> 01:32:40,750
11 o'clock.

1233
01:32:44,760 --> 01:32:46,710
Well, let me see, Mr Harrison.

1234
01:32:48,840 --> 01:32:51,140
I think we are on target, gentlemen.

1235
01:32:55,240 --> 01:32:57,510
Good. You're getting the hang of it now.

1236
01:32:58,880 --> 01:33:00,590
Sneaky!

1237
01:33:43,480 --> 01:33:45,430
January and February,

1238
01:33:45,520 --> 01:33:48,510
March and April...

1239
01:33:48,600 --> 01:33:50,550
June and July.

1240
01:33:56,240 --> 01:33:58,620
-They're going to kick you out soon.
-They can't.

1241
01:33:58,720 --> 01:34:01,150
I'm feeling particularly mad at the moment.

1242
01:34:01,240 --> 01:34:04,500
I don't think they cure that kind of madness here.

1243
01:34:05,480 --> 01:34:08,100
-What will you do?
-I don't know.

1244
01:34:09,000 --> 01:34:11,230
Pitch a tent outside the gates, I suppose.

1245
01:34:12,560 --> 01:34:15,670
Do you have any objections to a life under canvas?

1246
01:34:15,760 --> 01:34:17,710
Not more than a couple of thousand.

1247
01:34:19,480 --> 01:34:21,430
Seriously, though...

1248
01:34:21,520 --> 01:34:23,470
Seriously, though,

1249
01:34:24,560 --> 01:34:26,510
I've no idea.

1250
01:34:27,840 --> 01:34:29,590
It's just...

1251
01:34:30,480 --> 01:34:33,000
You could move in with me.

1252
01:34:33,600 --> 01:34:36,750
What, in the nurses' quarters?  Wouldn't Sister object?

1253
01:34:36,840 --> 01:34:39,590
Or do you imagine I'll wear some sort of disguise?

1254
01:34:39,880 --> 01:34:41,830
Don't be silly. It doesn't suit you.

1255
